Ogun State government yesterday took delivery of medical equipment worth N194million from the government of Czech Republic. The equipment include 15 ICU beds, an incubator, children cribs, a generator and a phototherapy machine. Handing over the equipment to Governor Dapo Abiodun at the Governor’s Office, Oke Mosan, Abeokuta, the Czech Republic Ambassador to Nigeria, Marek Skolil, expressed his home government’s delight to support and partner the state government, particularly in the area of health development. Skolil said the Czech government is concerned about how Nigeria, being the centerpiece of the regional architecture of Africa, was not developing not only in terms of infrastructure, but also in terms of human and social well-being. 